      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOIR (7) can keep up the top recent form following a slick 17.62 win two back with a Grade 5 victory at this track over 324m in 17.69. Running fast times and looks the one to beat again. CLOCK IT (1) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won by a nose at this track (17.76) beating Nan Said No in a Grade 5 on March 19. Likely to be about the mark. DESPICABLE GOAT (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (23.35) last time in a Mix 2/3 at Richmond. Solid record at the distance winning five races. The form out of his last race has been franked. A big run wouldn't surprise. KILCOY TIGER (3) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish here at this distance.",
